Create a spring boot application which should handle below

1. Create MVC Controller
2. Create REST Controller
3. Use RequestBody, ResponseBody, Requestentity, ResponseEntity annotations
4. Implement Bean validations(Hint:Use @Validated, @Valid and pattern)
5. Implement GlobalExceptionHandling(note:  handle both Controller & RestController exceptions)
6. Use Lombok library for removal of boilerplate code
7. Use @Slf4j annotation for logging
8. API should handle both xml and json responses
9. Use random port number to run multiple app instances .
10.Implement the content filter(Hint: @JsonIgnore,@JsonProperty)
11.Use H2 database for CRUD operations(use spring data for operations)(Hint:schema.sq and data.sql)
12.Migrate to MySQL 
13.Implement spring DATA derived query methods(hint: introducer & criteria clause)
14.Add support for auditing(Hint: createdBy,CreatedAt,updatedBy,updatedAt)
15.Use custom queries(Hint: @Query,@NamedQuery,@NamedNativeQuery & JPQL)
16.Implement communication b/n two rest services(RestTemplate,OpenFeign ,WebClient)
16.Implement profiling (hint: @ConfigurationProperties)
17.Leverage HAL explorer
18.expose Actuator endpoints
